doc.previous: North Dakota is primarily an agricultural state leading the country in the growth and production of several crops Barley canola corn flax soybeans sugar beets sunflowers and wheat are among the crops that are found in the state Cattle ranching and dairy ranching is common mainly in the south There is also a modest domestic winery industry in the state
